deck: A comic auteur from Finland. Real name: Juha Roikonen.
description:
He began to study graphic design at Design institute of Lahti (a Finnish place) in 1991.

He has been a comic freelancer since 1993.

He graduated in 1995.

His stories happen in one of those bizarre worlds, where pretty much anything can happen, and usually nobody is surprised that much. It`s also changing constantly.

His most famous creations are Jasso the cat and his tail.

He`s also illustrated Childrens books and drawn pictures for various Finnish magazines.

In 2005, he won a Puupäähattu (the most appreciated award for an extraordinary, Finish comic originator), which roughly translates to Blockheadhat. Other awards are Kirjailijakettu (rough translation: Authorfox)-award in 2006 and a prize in a comic making contest in 1983.
name: Jii Roikonen
